name: Which elements of the second array are not in the first array?
instruction:
The function `whatNotIncluded` takes two arrays consisting of strings or numbers.

The function should return an array of elements that are present in the second array but not in the first.

If one of the arrays is empty, the function should return the string "Array is empty".

If all elements of the second array are present in the first, the function should return an empty array.

Examples of function execution:
```javascript
whatNotIncluded([1, 2, 3], [1, 2, 3]) // []
whatNotIncluded([1, 2, 3], [1, 2, 3, 4]) // ["4"]
whatNotIncluded(["js", "needs", "more", "practice"], ["js", "js", "challenge"]) // ["js", "challenge"]
whatNotIncluded(["hello", "world"], ["js", "needs", "more", "practice"]) // ["js", "needs", "more", "practice"]
whatNotIncluded(["hello", "world"], []) // "Array is empty"
```

Hint:
The task is similar to the solution of previous tasks, but with slight changes.
When checking the property of an object, if the value is zero, the property should be removed from the object.

And output the keys of the object into an array.
